ts%20who%20are%20increasingly%20worried%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20human%20activities%20and%20severe%20droughts%20on%20this%20ecologically%20vital%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20still%20early%20to%20determine%20the%20cause%20of%20this%20extreme%20event%20but%20according%20to%20our%20experts%2C%20it%20is%20certainly%20connected%20to%20the%20drought%20period%20and%20high%20temperatures%20in%20Lake%20Tefe%2C%20in%20which%20some%20points%20are%20exceeding%2039%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2023%2F10%2F01%2Famericas%2Famazon-river-dolphins-dead-temperatures-drought-intl-hnk%2Findex.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20the%20Brazilian%20institute%20as%20saying%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20extreme%20weather%20has%20led%20to%20depleted%20water%20level%20in%20the%20Amazon%2C%20which%20is%20home%20to%20the%20world's%20largest%20tropical%20rainforest.%20It%20covers%20over%205.5%20million%20square%20kilometres%2C%20which%20is%20roughly%20the%20size%20of%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20drought%20in%20the%20region%20is%20affecting%20100%2C000%20people.%20Boats%20can%20still%20travel%20on%20sections%20with%20severely%20depleted%20water%20level%2C%20but%20the%20Brazilian%20government%20is%20setting%20up%20a%20task%20force%20to%20help%20those%20who%20rely%20on%20the%20river%20as%20transport%20route%20for%20food%20and%20other%20essentials.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EExperts%20are%20trying%20to%20relocate%20surviving%20dolphins%20by%20transferring%20them%20from%20lagoons%20and%20ponds%20to%20the%20main%20river%20where%20the%20water%20is%20cooler%2C%20%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E%20further%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20some%20environmentalists%20have%20raised%20concerns.%20%26quot%3BTransferring%20river%20dolphins%20to%20other%20rivers%20is%20not%20that%20safe%20because%20it's%20important%20to%20verify%20if%20toxins%20or%20viruses%20are%20present%20before%20releasing%20the%20animals%20into%20the%20wild