r%20Creator%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESince%201901%2C%20Nobel%20prizes%20have%20been%20awarded%20to%20men%2C%20women%20and%20organisations%20for%20work%20that%20has%20led%20to%20great%20advances%20for%20mankind%2C%20in%20line%20with%20the%20wishes%20of%20inventor%20Alfred%20Nobel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fnobel-prizes-this-week-to-illuminate-bleak-year-for-world-peace-4441604%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewinners%20of%20this%20year's%20prizes%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20be%20announced%20daily%20from%20Monday%2C%20October%202%20through%20October%209.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20five%20things%20to%20know%20about%20the%20prizes%20and%20their%20creator.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENobel%20laureates%20prevented%20from%20attending%20ceremony%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%201901%2C%20six%20Nobel%20peace%20laureates%20have%20been%20prevented%20from%20attending%20the%20prize%20ceremony%20in%20Oslo.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201936%2C%20German%20journalist%20and%20pacifist%20Carl%20Von%20Ossietzky%20was%20detained%20in%20a%20Nazi%20concentration%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201975%2C%20Soviet%20leaders%20refused%20to%20allow%20Russian%20dissident%20Andrei%20Sakharov%20to%20travel%20to%20Oslo%20to%20pick%20up%20his%20prize.%20He%20was%20represented%20by%20his%20wife%20Yelena%20Bonner.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201983%2C%20Polish%20union%20leader%20Lech%20Walesa%20declined%20the%20invitation%20to%20come%20to%20Oslo%20for%20fear%20he%20would%20not%20be%20allowed%20back%20into%20Poland.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201991%2C%20Myanmar%20opposition%20leader%20Aung%20San%20Suu%20Kyi%20was%20under%20house%20arrest%20when%20she%20won%20the%20prize.%20Given%20permission%20by%20the%20junta%20to%20travel%2C%20she%20also%20declined%20for%20fear%20of%20not%20being%20able%20to%20return%20to%20her%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202010%2C%20Chinese%20dissident%20Liu%20Xiaobo%20was%20in%20prison.%20His%20chai