2520Laphonza%2520Butler%2520will%2520replace%2Cever%2520serve%2520in%2520the%2520Senate.%5C%22%3ESan%20Francisco%20Chronicle%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20first%20openly%20gay%20U.S.%20senator%20from%20California%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fpolitics%2Felections%2Fgavin-newsom-to-appoint-laphonza-butler-to-fill-dianne-feinsteins-senate-seat-16a9c61b%5C%22%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWho%20is%20Laphonza%20Butler%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EButler%20is%20currently%20the%20president%20of%20EMILYs%20List%2C%20an%20organization%20working%20to%20get%20Democratic%2C%20pro-choice%20women%20elected%20to%20state%20and%20nationwide%20offices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPreviously%2C%20Butler%20worked%20as%20a%20policy%20director%20for%20Airbnb%20and%20political%20consulting%20firm%20SCRB%20Strategies%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Femilyslist.org%2Four-leadership%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eher%20EMILY's%20List%20biography.%3C%2Fa%3E%20At%20SCRB%2C%20she%20worked%20alongside%20Newsom's%20most%20prominent%20strategists%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fpolitics%2Fla-pol-ca-laphonza-butler-20181207-story.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELA%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20was%20a%20senior%20advisor%20for%20current%20US%20Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris's%202020%20presidential%20campaign%20and%20in%20Hillary%20Clinton's%202008%20and%202016%20presidential%20campaigns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20has%20extensive%20experience%20in%20labor%20activism%2C%20and%20served%20as%20president%20of%20SEIU%20Local%202015%2C%20which%20represents%20long-term%20caregivers%20in%20California%2C%20for%20nearly%20a%20decade.%20During%20her%20time%20there%2C%20she%20advocated%20to%20raise%20the%20state's%20minimum%20wage%20to%20%2415%20an%20hour%2C%20per%20her%20EMILYs%20List%20bio.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EButler%20shares%20a%20significant%20history%20with%20Harris%2C%20per%20the%20Times.%20The%20two%20met%20in%202010%20when%20Harris%20was%20campaigning%20for%20CA%20attorney%20general.%20In%20the%20primary%20for%20that%20election%2C%20Butler%20helped%20Harris%20get%20a%20triple%20endorsement%20from%20her%20union.%20When%20Harris%20won%2C%20she%20said%20Butler%20was%20a%20supporter%20from%20the%20start%20of%20her%20campaign%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fpolitics%2Fla-pol-ca-laphonza-butler-20181207-story.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20the%20LA%20Times.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%202018%20to%202021%2C%20Butler%20served%20as%20a%20Regent%20for%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20per%20the%20Board%20of%20Regents%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fregents.universityofcalifornia.edu%2Fabout%2Fmembers-and-advisors%2Fbios%2Flaphonza-butler.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite.%20%3C%2Fa%3EShe%20received%20her%20Bachelor's%20degree%20in%20Political%20Science%20from%20Jackson%20State%20University%20in%202001%2C%20per%20her%20LinkedIn.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EButler%20has%20previous%20connections%20to%20Newsom%20outside%20of%20SCRB%20%E2%80%94%20at%20one%20point%2C%20she%20was%20being%20considered%20for%20the%20position%20of%20his%20chief%20of%20staff%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F09%2F29%2Ffeinstein-death-senate-seat-contest-00119079%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPolitico.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224443%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20late%20Sen.%20Dianne%20Feinstein%20on%20April%204%2C%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651a3b4fec74fc001906fc75%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223332%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20late%20Sen.%20Dianne%20Feinstein%20on%20April%204%2C%202022.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FJ.%20Scott%20App