2_blank%5C%22%3EBBC%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMuch%20like%20they%20have%20done%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20world%2C%20the%20rats%20and%20goats%20contributed%20to%20the%20deforestation%20and%20desertification%20of%20Redonda%20and%20are%20blamed%20for%20the%20extinction%20of%20the%20endemic%20skink%20and%20iguana%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20extirpation%20of%20the%20Antiguan%20burrowing%20owl%20on%20the%20island%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20Environmental%20Awareness%20Group%20(EAG)%2C%20an%20Antigua%20and%20Barbuda%20NGO.%20%26quot%3BBy%202012%2C%20the%20ecosystem%20was%20so%20severely%20degraded%20that%20even%20the%20feral%20goats%20were%20starving%20to%20death.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20environmental%20groups%20such%20as%20EAG%20launched%20restoration%20efforts%20to%20bring%20back%20the%20local%20plant%20life%20and%20animal%20species%20native%20to%20the%20island.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plan%20included%20relocating%20Redonda's%20estimated%2060%20goats%20to%20Antigua%20and%20eradicating%20about%207%2C000%20rats%20with%20the%20help%20of%20local%20and%20international%20volunteers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20all%20we%20did.%20We%20just%20removed%20the%20species%20that%20were%20not%20supposed%20to%20be%20there%20and%20within%20months%20we%20saw%20the%20vegetation%20growing%20back%20%E2%80%94%20the%20island%20rebounding%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnella%20Bradshaw%2C%20EAG's%20Redonda%20program%20coordinator%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F09%2F29%2Ftravel%2Fredonda-caribbean-restoration-wildlife-c2e-scn-spc-intl%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20just%20two%20years%2C%20entire%20species%20began%20to%20return%2C%20according%20to%20the%20EAG.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithin%2024%20months%20of%20invasive%20species%20removal%2C%20populations%20of%20at%20least%20two%20of%20the%20three%20lizard%20species%20have%20increased%20by%20more%20than%20threefold%20and%20species%20of%20land%20birds%20and%20invertebrates%2C%20not%20seen%20in%20decades%2C%20have%20returned%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20NGO%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Redonda%20is%20home%20to%20dozens%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-second-for-most-number-of-endangered-species-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethreatened%20species%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20seabirds%20that%20haven't%20been%20seen%20in%20centuries.%20Total%20plant%20biomass%20has%20increased%20by%20more%20than%202%2C000%25%2C%20CNN%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUp%20to%20this%20date%2C%20we%20haven't%20planted%20anything%2C%20we%20haven't%20reintroduced%20any%20species.%20We%20just%20removed%20the%20rats%20and%20the%20goats%2C%20and%20the%20island%20transformed%20right%20in%20front%20of%20our%20eyes%2C%26quot%3B%20Bradshaw%20told%20CNN.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20month%2C%20the%20government%20of%20Antigua%20and%20Barbuda%20established%20the%20Redonda%20Ecosystem%20Reserve%20which%20will%20cover%2030%2C000%20hectares%20or%2074%2C000%20acres%20of%20land%20and%20sea%2C%20including%20the%20small%20island.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBradshaw%20told%20the%20outlet%20that%20this%20designation%20should%20help%20the%20island%20continue%20its%20restoration%2C%20which%20remains%20fragile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20EAG%20spokesperson%20did%20not%20return%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaribbean-island-redonda-rats-restoration-wildlife-endangered-species-antigua-barbuda-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696203833000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6519fa26ec74fc001906f9ce%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaribbean-island-redonda-rats-restoration-wildlife-endangered-species-antigua-barbuda-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20tiny