le%20With%20Acute%20Drug%20Shortages%2C%20Govt%20Denies%20but%20WHO%20Worried%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F07%2F26171035%2Ftb_PTI.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20an%20unusual%20repetition%20of%20sorts%2C%20the%20Union%20health%20ministry%20issued%20a%20press%20release%20on%20Sunday%2C%20October%201%2C%20denying%20any%20shortages%20of%20essential%20medicines%20for%20drug-resistant%20TB%20patients.%20It%20was%20only%20on%20September%2026%20that%20the%20ministry%20issued%20an%20almost%20similar%20statement.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20have%20been%20some%20media%20reports%20claiming%20a%20shortage%20of%20anti-TB%20drugs%20in%20India.%20Such%20reports%20are%20false%2C%20misleading%2C%20motivated%20and%20seem%20deliberately%20intended%20to%20deceive%20and%20misguide%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20claimed%20the%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20release%20on%20October%201.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20didn%E2%80%99t%20specify%20which%20media%20report%20it%20was%20referring%20to%20and%20when%20it%20was%20published.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fwill-the-un-high-level-meeting-address-indias-problem-of-tb-drugs-stock-out-situation%5C%22%3EUnprecedented%20TB%20Drugs%20Stock-Out%20in%20India%3A%20Union%20Health%20Minister%20Skips%20UN%20High-Level%20Meet%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIncidentally%2C%20the%20second%20press%20release%20came%20only%20two%20days%20after%20113%20global%20TB%20organisations%20and%20more%20than%20700%20TB%20advocates%20from%20across%20the%20globe%20had%20dispatched%20a%20joint%20appeal%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20seeking%20his%20urgent%20invention%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20stock-outs%20in%20India.%20These%20organisations%20were%20located%20in%20the%20US%2C%20UK%2C%20India%2C%20Zambia%2C%20Malawi%2C%20Canada%2C%20Uganda%20and%20several%20others.%20Their%20letter%20can%20be%20read%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Ftb-drugs-shortage-113-global-bodies-write-to-pm-modi-seek-his-urgent-intervention%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehere%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETalking%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20October%201%2C%20Blessina%20Kumar%2C%20associated%20with%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fcompany%2Fglobal-coalition-of-tb-advocates%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EGlobal%20Coalition%20of%20TB%20Activists%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20one%20of%20the%20signatories%20of%20the%20letter%2C%20said%20that%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Office%20has%20so%20far%20not%20responded%20to%20the%20letter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20October%201%20statement%20claimed%20all%20necessary%20drugs%20were%20available%20in%20adequate%20stock%20%E2%80%93%20sourcing%20data%20from%20the%20Nikshay%20app.%20It%20made%20a%20similar%20claim%20in%20the%20September%2026%20statement.%20The%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20full%20statement%20issued%20on%20October%201%20can%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1962655%5C%22%3Eread%3C%2Fa%3E%20here%20and%20the%20September%2026%20one%20here%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleseDetail.aspx%3FPRID%3D1960787%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehere%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Activists%20working%20with%20TB%20control%20say%20there%20is%20no%20way%20to%20independently%20verify%20the%20government-issued%20figures.%20They%20maintain%20that%20they%20continue%20to%20remain%20flooded%20with%20SOS%20calls%20from%20patients%20who%20are%20unable%20to%20get%20drugs.%20The%20two%20statements%20appear%20identical%20in%20many%20ways.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%